service: Low Income Home Energy Assistance Program
description:
The Low Income Home Energy Assistance Program (LIHEAP) is operated by the New Jersey Department of Community Affairs (DCA). It provides financial assistance to very low-income residents for their heating and cooling bills. The program's assistance is available from October 1 to September 30 each year. 

To apply for assistance, individuals must first check their eligibility by reviewing the Energy Assistance Program Fact Sheet and Income Guidelines. If eligible, they must complete and submit an application to their local Community Action Agency. Applicants can find local agency contact information and further assistance by calling the toll-free hotline at 1-800-510-3102.

service: Medicare Part D: Low Income Subsidy (LIS)
description: The Division of Aging Services is located in Trenton, NJ, at 222 South Warren Street, PO Box 700. There are no specific operating hours mentioned. To qualify for assistance with Medicare costs, individuals must meet certain income and asset criteria. For example, to benefit from a Medicare Savings Program, a single person's annual income must not exceed $20,340, and a couple's must not exceed $27,600. Additionally, applicants may need to provide information regarding their assets, which cannot exceed $9,430 for individuals or $14,130 for couples, excluding their home and car.
